{/* Card #1 */}

Introduction

What are Networked Lighting Controls?

{/* Hidden modal content */}

Overview

Network lighting controls allow all your fixtures within your facility to communicate with each other. This enables grouping, motion sensing, dimming, and more, providing energy savings and operational flexibility.

Advantages of Networked Lighting Controls

  • Energy Savings: Additional 50-70% savings after converting to LED.
  • Wireless Implementation: No need for rewiring, reducing installation costs.
  • Multiple Control Strategies: Grouping, dimming, scheduling, and more for enhanced control.
  • Incentives: Additional utility incentives for upgrading to networked lighting controls.

Why Choose Jarvis?

Jarvis provides hardware-ready fixtures, software for implementation, and full support through design and implementation phases. We simplify networked lighting controls to help you succeed.

{/* Card #2 */}

Success Guide

How to have smooth NLC projects.

{/* Hidden modal content */}

Success Guide

How to successfully plan a project to use Network Lighting Controls:

  • Understand the Software: Get trained on what Jarvis Link can do and understand the hardware needed to accomplish your goals.
  • Talk to Your Customers: Learn what they need so the project fits their goals.
  • Group Your Fixtures: Plan how to group fixtures based on feedback.
  • Training: We can train you on the app or commission the system for you.

For more information, visit{' '} Jarvis Link. Planning and preparation are key to success.

{/* Card #3 */}

Software

What is Jarvis Link?

{/* Hidden modal content */}

What is Jarvis Link?

Jarvis Link is an advanced network lighting control system designed to connect and manage lighting fixtures within a facility.

Core Capabilities

  • Lighting Zones: Group multiple fixtures for collective control.
  • Brightness and Dimming Control: Adjust lighting levels for energy efficiency.
  • Automated Responses: Set lights to respond automatically to inactivity.

Mapping and Project Management

Jarvis Link includes a map feature for large-scale projects, making setup and ongoing management easier.

Learning and Support

The system is user-friendly, with training available to ensure you can fully leverage its capabilities.

The Benefits of Jarvis Link

Jarvis Link offers major energy savings and operational efficiency, suitable for many facility types.

{/* Card #4 */}

Jarvis Link

Quick start guide.

{/* Hidden modal content */}

Getting Started with Jarvis Link

Jarvis Link is designed to streamline the process of setting up networked lighting controls.

Step 1: Register and Install

Begin by registering for Jarvis Link and downloading the app on your Apple device.

Step 2: Create a New Project

In the app, create a project for your lighting control activities.

Step 3: Define Areas

Break your project into areas to organize lighting controls more easily.

Step 4: Add Zones and Profiles

Group fixtures in zones, choose the right profile, and place zones on your map.

Step 5: Assign Fixtures

Add fixtures to the zones. The light blinks to confirm itâ€™s being selected.

Step 6: Adjust Settings

Fine-tune lighting behaviors like dimming and scheduling to match your needs.

Visit{' '} Jarvis Link {' '} for more info and support.

Transforming Office and Warehouse Lighting

Jarvis Link is designed to optimize lighting in both office and warehouse environments.

Office Environment

Lights turn on with occupancy. Use kinetic switches to dim lights for meetings.

Warehouse Environment

Large areas are lit only when needed, saving energy.

Comprehensive Control

Jarvis Link delivers efficiency, flexibility, and comfort.
